## 9. Suggestions & Tips (Dissertation: Future Work, Methodology)

- **Checkpointing:** Save intermediate model checkpoints, as Colab sessions can disconnect.
- **Frame extraction:** Consider extracting frames only once per video and referencing their paths (current code does this).
- **Metadata handling:** Use `metadata.csv` if available for more flexible labeling.
- **Memory handling:** Use `pin_memory=True` in DataLoaders and reduce batch size if you hit CUDA OOM errors.
- **EfficientNet vs XceptionNet:** Comment on architecture differences in your dissertation’s Discussion section.
- **Grad-CAM:** Use qualitative GradCAM images in Results/Interpretability section.
- **Scaling up:** For larger datasets or more frames, consider Google Colab Pro or cloud VMs.

